  <summary>3/2/2005--Introduced.
Direct Deposit Savings Act of 2005 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to permit taxpayers to direct that any overpayment of taxes be: (1) refunded in part by check, draft, or similar paper instrument; (2) allocated in part among not more than four accounts; and (3) deposited by electronic fund transfer in the accounts to which allocated.</summary>
